FuncDef: If different from default, this command overrides the value specified byl2-ap-encap-typeon wlan-gw level. See the description of l2-ap-encap-type for more detail. This value can only be changed while the l2-ap is shutdown.

ParaDef.Info: Specifies to use the value specified by l2-ap-encap-type.
Specifies to use both the SAP and the AP are not VLAN-tagged.
Specifies to use either the AP or the SAP uses one VLAN tag.
Up to two VLAN tags are used by the AP or SAP.
